				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Forever ?<br /><br />External devices are supposed to pull the IRQ line low when they want to have attention of the processor, and then the processor is supposed to, with the help of memory-mapped I/O, acknownledge the IRQ, and tell the device it can release the IRQ line. Thus even if the 'I' flag is set, the IRQ is never missed, the device keeps waiting for the processor to get attention until an acknowledge happens.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

