					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, you can't forget about IRQs just because they aren't supposed to be serviced right away. IIRC, the CPU tests for IRQs every instruction.<br /><br />As for pulling the IRQ line back up, that's up to the device that pulled it low, and the most common approach is to implement an &quot;IRQ acknowledgement&quot; register, so the program itself can let the device know that the IRQ has been handled.</div>

